headline.main: ARRIVAL OF THE ILLINOIS.; Later from South America and Australia. $495,440 in Specie on Freight. INTERESTING FROM THE ISTHMUS.

docs.lead_paragraph: Steamer Illinois, JAMES McKINSTRY, U.S. Navy, commander, sailed from New-York for Aspinwall vid Kingston May 20 at 2 1/2 o'clock P. M., arrived at Kingston 27th ult. at 6 o'clock P.M., sailed thence 28th ult. at 9 1/2 o'clock A.M., arriving at Aspinwall 30th ult. at 7 o'clock P.M.; sailed again for New-York May 31, at 1 o'clock P.M.
